            <td bgcolor="#0075cc"><font size="-1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Come on baby, Light my fire.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   </strong><br>
              <font size="-2">Posted by:Mr Smarty Pants               </font> </font><font size="-2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">on:11/21/2004 at:10:09:48 AM <nbsp><nbsp> PST</font></td>
          </tr>
          <tr> 
            <td bgcolor="#e6e6e6"><header><br>

So many new faces mean only one thing: more ugly people. Ok I guess it can mean two things: more ugly people and new game releases. Rather than focus on the inordinate amount of truly hideous people we are adding to our ranks, I will focus instead on the “new games” and the spelling of the word “truly”. <br><br>


TRULY is spelled without an E. It is NOT spelled truely or truley. As much as I enjoy tormenting people who can’t spell any better than any typical pimple faced teenager picked at random from the bowels of any metropolitan high school, this word simply needs to stop being abused. Think of the kittens. For greater reference on how to not be an idiot, I recommend this website: http://www.m-w.com/ <br><br>


And before I get into the “new game” thing I also wanted to point out the misuse of the word “ding”. While I appreciate that people want to share their excitement upon leveling or gaining a new AA point, yelling “DING” in guildchat or shout is the virtual equivalent of yelling “congratulate me on achieving a meaningless task because I am insecure, and I need the reassurance to make my life complete”. <br><br>


ANY MONKEY WITH HALF A BRAIN can level in EQ1, EQ2 and virtually any other game. They are DESIGNED to make you level. That’s the POINT of the game, you fucking idiot. Do you yell “DING” at home when you level in Diablo II? With some rare exceptions I would guess not. It only seems to be that people need to share a sense of meaningless accomplishments when other people (that more than likely don’t give a flying fuck) are around.<br><br>
 

And those of you that CONGRATULATE others for yelling “DING” aren’t helping any. But to be fair, you are probably in the group of people that need a virtual pat on the back for accomplishing a virtual task that any retarded 5 year old can do too. Here is my suggestion: Save your “DING” shouts for important events. Capping your level to 70 is worthy of a DING. Making your 500th AA is worthy of a DING. Making your class level in EQ2 is worthy of a DING. EVERY OTHER LEVEL IS NOT WORTHY OF ME TAKING THIRTY SECONDS OF MY LIFE TO TELL YOU HOW FUCKING SPLENDID YOU ARE SO YOU DON’T BREAK DOWN INTO TEARS AT YOUR OWN WORTHLESS EXISTENCE! Seriously... no one really cares that you made level 8 when I can do it in under two hours on a Percocet and two beers. <br><br>


Fucking “DING”bats! <br><br>


Calm… calm… deep breath…. <br><br>


New games... <br><br>


Every single time a new game comes out, people panic. THE SKY IS FALLING THE SKY IS FALLING! Haha! I bet a bunch of you wankers ducked! Look kids, the sky is just fucking fine. New games come and new games go. After playing EverQuest for almost SEVEN years, I have seen it all. Guilds who used to be uber and L337 are suddenly empty shells because all of their flaky idiot “leaders” (using that term very loosely) have suddenly vanished off the face of the earth. Or they decide that they don’t want anyone ELSE to have fun while they are gone so they delete the guild.<br><br>
 

Yeah. MMMAYBE that should tell you something about your choice of guild, bunky. Maybe it tells you something about your own choices in life. Always choosing the most flashy things in life isn’t the best way to go, and going to a guild that caters to large egos who think they are the shit usually ends up exactly like that…shit. <br><br>


As for Grey Hawke… we proudly call ourselves the “Tortoise Guild”. We may not get to everything first. But then again, we don’t burn out like the flames of a gay summer fling either. We are probably the oldest original guild on Karana at this point. Grey Hawke has been around and WILL be around for a long time. We may have occasionally caused undue turmoil among some guilds, but we have overwhelmingly outlasted those fly-by-night “ego guilds” because we remain constant. Constant, honorable, and realistic in the needs and wants of our guildmates. You just can’t ask for more than that in my opinion. <br><br>


Grey Hawke will be here until EQ is dead and buried. Count on it. And for those of you wondering if you made the wrong guild choice… as long as you aren’t an asshole, and you want to have fun seeing this game to its fullest (eventually) come give us a try. Ask an officer if you can join a raid. This is a golden opportunity to join a long-standing guild led by officers that give a damn about fairness and integrity, and passing it up may be a wasted opportunity for many of you that would fit in well. <br><br>


The rest of you can burn in the lowest depths of Kelethin (hell). <br><br>


Rah rah rah and all that shit! <br><br>

<\header></td>
